'''Juan Kotz<U+00E9>''' (born {{birth date|1992|05|18|df=y}} in [[Messina]], [[South Africa]]) is a South African [[rugby union]] player, currently playing with the {{Rut Falcons}}.<ref name="SARU Player Profile Juan Kotz<U+00E9>">{{cite web | url=http://www.sarugby.net/playerprofile.aspx?id=44965 | title=SARU Player Profile Juan Kotz<U+00E9> | work=South African Rugby Union | accessdate=18 July 2014}}</ref> His regular position is fly-half.

==Career==

===Youth and Varsity Cup rugby===

In 2008, he was selected for the {{Rut Limpopo Blue Bulls}} side that played at the Under-16 Grant Khomo Week tournament in [[Ermelo]]. He was subsequently selected in a South African Under-16 Elite squad.

He then joined [[East Rand]]-based outfit the {{Rut Falcons}}. During the second half of 2011, he played for the {{Rut Falcons U19}} side in the [[2011 Under-19 Provincial Championship]], the {{Rut Falcons U21}} side in the [[2011 Under-21 Provincial Championship]] and for the senior side.

He also played some [[Varsity Cup]] rugby. In [[2014 Varsity Rugby#Varsity Cup|2014]], he represented {{Rut UJ}} in the Varsity Cup competition, making six appearances.

===Falcons===

His first class debut came in their [[2011 Currie Cup First Division]] match against the {{Rut Boland Cavaliers}} in [[Kempton Park, Gauteng|Kempton Park]], where he contributed eight points with the boot.<ref name="Match Breakdown: Valke vs Regent Boland Cavaliers">{{cite web | url=http://www.sarugby.net/matchbreakdown.aspx?id=20218&category=&leagueid=810&homeid=8551&awayid=8554&fullview=true | title=Match Breakdown: Valke vs Regent Boland Cavaliers | work=South African Rugby Union | date=10 September 2011 | accessdate=24 July 2014}}</ref> He made a total of five starts for the Falcons during the competition, scoring 47 points.<ref name="2011 Currie Cup First Division top scorers">{{cite web | url=http://www.sarugby.net/scorers.aspx?categoryid=sarugby/curriecup&leagueid=810&fullview=true | title=2011 Currie Cup First Division top scorers | publisher=South African Rugby Union | accessdate=24 July 2014}}</ref> This included an 18-point haul in their match against the {{Rut SWD Eagles}} in Kempton Park<ref name="Match Breakdown: Valke vs SWD Eagles">{{cite web | url=http://www.sarugby.net/matchbreakdown.aspx?id=20222&category=&leagueid=810&homeid=8551&awayid=8550&fullview=true | title=Match Breakdown: Valke vs SWD Eagles | work=South African Rugby Union | date=24 September 2011 | accessdate=24 July 2014}}</ref>

Six appearances followed in the [[2012 Vodacom Cup]] competition, with a tally of 59 points putting him in eighth place on the scoring charts.<ref name="2012 Vodacom Cup top scorers">{{cite web | url=http://www.sarugby.net/scorers.aspx?categoryid=sarugby/vodacomcup&leagueid=1211&fullview=true | title=2012 Vodacom Cup top scorers | publisher=South African Rugby Union | accessdate=24 July 2014}}</ref> He scored 35 points in ten appearances <U+2013> mostly being used as a substitute during the [[2012 Currie Cup First Division]].

40 points in seven appearances followed in the [[2013 Vodacom Cup]] before he scored 90 points for the Falcons during the [[2013 Currie Cup First Division]] to end as their top scorer and fifth overall.<ref name="2013 Currie Cup First Division top scorers">{{cite web | url=http://www.sarugby.net/scorers.aspx?categoryid=sarugby/curriecup&leagueid=1304&fullview=true | title=2013 Currie Cup First Division top scorers | publisher=South African Rugby Union | accessdate=24 July 2014}}</ref>

He topped the scoring charts during the [[2014 Currie Cup qualification]] series, scoring 91 points in just six appearances, which included scoring 22 points in one match against the {{Rut SWD Eagles}}.<ref name="Match Breakdown: South Western Districs vs Valke">{{cite web | url=http://www.sarugby.net/matchbreakdown.aspx?id=119474&category=&leagueid=1774&homeid=18034&awayid=18084&fullview=true | title=Match Breakdown: South Western Districs vs Valke | work=South African Rugby Union | date=20 June 2014 | accessdate=24 July 2014}}</ref>

